
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-perez-abfab-wg-arch-erp-00.txt'>
    <title>"ERP extensions for the ABFAB architecture", Alejandro Perez-Mendez, Rafael Lopez, Gabriel Lopez-Millan, Fernando Pereniguez-Garcia</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-perez-abfab-wg-arch-erp-00.txt</link>
    <description>The Application Bridging for Federated Access Beyond Web (ABFAB) architecture [I-D.ietf-abfab-arch] allows the use of EAP to perform access control to a wide range of applications.  This document describes the extensions required to incorporate support for the EAP Extensions for the EAP Re-authentication Protocol (ERP) to this architecture, in order to provide an enhanced fast re-authentication and Single Sign-On (SSO) support and a better resource utilization. Authorization aspects are also described.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-10-27T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
